turn.2: JWH-210 JWH-210 is an analgesic chemical from the naphthoylindole family, which acts as a potent cannabinoid agonist at both the CB and CB receptors, with K values of 0.46 nM at CB and 0.69 nM at CB.
turn.3: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.4: It is one of the most potent 4-substituted naphthoyl derivatives in the naphthoylindole series, having a higher binding affinity (i.e. lower K) at CB than both its 4-methyl and 4-"n"-propyl homologues JWH-122 (CB K 0.69 nM) and JWH-182 (CB K 0.65 nM) respectively, and than the 4-methoxy compound JWH-081 (CB K 1.2 nM).
turn.6: It was discovered by and named after John W. Huffman.
turn.8: JWH-210 may be neurotoxic to animals when administered in high doses.
turn.10: In the United States, all CB receptor agonists of the 3-(1-naphthoyl)indole class such as JWH-210 are Schedule I Controlled Substances.
turn.11: What else is notable about it?
turn.12: JWH-210 and JWH-122 were banned in Sweden on 1 October 2010 as hazardous goods harmful to health, after being identified as ingredients in "herbal" synthetic cannabis products.
